Using IBM 1.3.1, and the following test program, on F2. I placed a line 
breakpoint on the "println" statement with a condition of "i == 3". When I 
launched the program, it appeared to be suspended. The main thread allowed me 
to "resume", but was not showing any stack frames. When I resumed, it did one 
loop and hung again. I could pause the main thread, but I could not step or 
resume properly. Had to terminate & remove the program.

public class InfiniteLoop {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		int i = 0;
		while (true) {
			System.out.println("Looping " + i);
			i++;
			try {
				Thread.sleep(750);
			} catch (InterruptedException e) {
			}
		}
	}
}
